Mpho Raborife, News24(Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Sassa, the Department of Social Development and Cash Paymaster Services (CPS) have come to an agreement over a payment plan for 17 million social grant beneficiaries starting from April 1.The agreement was reached after three days of "intense" negotiation between all three parties, department spokesperson Lumka Oliphant said on Friday night.Further details about the nature of the agreement would be revealed by Social Development Minister Bathabile Dlamini in due course, Oliphant said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.